> IMO, homam does not *directly* help you control your vices. It is a
> wonderful supplement, but you need to actively work on other things as well.
> In sandhyAvandanam, one of the things we do is say "kAmo.akArShIt.
> manyurakArShIt". (Desire did it ... Anger did it). We say this exactly once
> in atonement of sins. Like many things in sandhyAvandana, this is a
> "technique" that you can use. Saying it once, 10 times or 100 times in a row
> during sandhyAvandana is of limited use. In fact, it is practically useless.
> But, there is a way to make it extremely useful. Try saying it every time
> after you realize that anger controlled you. Then, after some time, try
> saying it while you are mad. Then, after some time, try saying it just
> before you get mad. Using it this way, by saying this mantra 10 times
> throughout the day is more useful than saying it 100 times in a row each
> morning. Just my 2 cents.
